#Approach:
Rotate Image by 90 Degree Clockwise – Approach

Matrix ko 90 degree clockwise rotate karne ke liye do steps use karte hain:
Transpose + Reverse each row.

Step 1: Transpose the matrix
Transpose ka matlab hota hai matrix[i][j] ko matrix[j][i] se swap karna.
Isse rows columns me convert ho jaati hain.

Step 2: Har row ko reverse kar do
Transpose ke baad agar hum har row ko reverse kar denge,
to matrix 90 degree clockwise rotate ho jayega.

Example:
1 2 3
4 5 6
7 8 9

Transpose:
1 4 7
2 5 8
3 6 9

Reverse rows:
7 4 1
8 5 2
9 6 3

Time Complexity: O(n^2)
Space Complexity: O(1) (In-place rotation)

#Code:
class Solution {

    private void swap(int[][] matrix, int row1, int col1, int row2, int col2){
        if (row1 < 0 || row1 >= matrix.length || col1 < 0 || col1 >= matrix[row1].length ||
            row2 < 0 || row2 >= matrix.length || col2 < 0 || col2 >= matrix[row2].length) {
            System.out.println("Error: Indices are out of bounds.");
            return;
        }

        int temp = matrix[row1][col1];
        matrix[row1][col1] = matrix[row2][col2];
        matrix[row2][col2] = temp;
    }

    public void rotate(int[][] matrix) {
        //Step-1: Transpose matrix
        int n = matrix.length;
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            for(int j=i+1; j<n; j++){
                swap(matrix, i, j, j, i);
            }
        }

        //Step-2: reverse the arrays
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            int start = 0;
            int end = matrix[i].length - 1;
            while(start < end){
                int temp = matrix[i][start];
                matrix[i][start] = matrix[i][end];
                matrix[i][end] = temp;
                start++;
                end--;
            } 
        }
    }
}
